title: Status for desktop does not start when port 5000 is in use
body: When a different application is running on port 5000 already, Status desktop does not start. Instead it either hangs in this screen or does not even show a screen. It does neither crash nor show an error message. ## How to reproduce 1. Block the port with `python3 -m http.server 5000` 2. Start Status dektop ## Logs The fun thing is that Status sends stuff to that port (owned by another application), like: ``` Serving HTTP on 0.0.0.0 port 5000 (http://0.0.0.0:5000/) ... 127.0.0.1 - -
